list.abstract: carry是Dota中以物理攻击为主，并且可以独立与几个人抗衡的英雄。 carry在LOL泛指的就是主力输出型的英雄，一般英雄分类可以分为肉(坦克)、carry(输出)、ganker(游走的)，辅助，大部分英雄其实是可以混搭的，比如半肉半输出，或者辅助输出之类的。
carry是一个英语单词，为动词、名词，作动词时意为“拿，扛；携带；支持；搬运；能达到；被携带；被搬运”；作名词时意为“运载；[计] 进位；射程；(Carry)人名；(英)卡里”。

yingyinNormal.en: I'm happy to carry it for you. You're scaring me.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我很乐意帮你拿。你吓到我了。

yingyinNormal.en: This is serious, son. When you carry this axe, you carry all of us with you.
yingyinNormal.zh: 这件事很重要，当你拿着这把斧头就背负着维京人的责任。

yingyinNormal.en: You carry the bucket, Peppa. And I'll hold the torch. Don't stay out too late, Grandpa Pig. OK, Granny Pig.
yingyinNormal.zh: 你拿着这个桶，佩奇。我来拿着手电筒。不要在外面呆太久，猪爷爷。好的，猪奶奶。

yingyinNormal.en: I'm Susie Moss. Fourth grade, glasses, I used to carry around a box of animal crackers like a purse.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我是苏西莫斯，四年级呀，戴眼镜，我常常像拿手提包一样拿一包动物饼干。

yingyinNormal.en: George, I'll pick up the sticks and you can carry them. Collecting sticks is fun! Good. That's enough sticks.
yingyinNormal.zh: 乔治，我来捡木柴。你帮我拿着它们。收集棍子太好玩啦！很好这些木柴够了。

yingyinNormal.en: So they handed me a cornett, which is fine by me because it's easier to play. The case was a lot lighter to carry around.

yingyinNormal.en: Jolly good. Carry on. What's Miss Rabbit doing? She's recycling all the rusty, old cars. Who can tell me which bin the bottles go in? The green one. That's right.

examination_example.sentence: "Give up TV" or "<highlight>Carry</highlight> a book with you at all times."
examination_example.sentence_trans: “放弃电视”或“随身携带一本书。”

examination_example.sentence: "<highlight>Carry</highlight> a book with you at all times" can actually work, too — providing you dip in often enough.
examination_example.sentence_trans: “随身携带一本书”实际上也能起到作用——只要你经常沉浸其中。

examination_example.sentence: Airborne technologies, such as photographic equipment <highlight>carried</highlight> by airplanes or spacecraft, allow archaeologists to learn about what lies beneath the ground without digging.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 航空技术，如飞机或宇宙飞船携带的摄影设备，使考古学家不用挖掘就能了解地下的东西。

sense_info_list.zh: (carry out)实施; 执行; 实现

examination_example.sentence: To <highlight>carry</highlight> it out before the year of 2020.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 在2020年前实施。

examination_example.sentence: Because it didn't want to <highlight>carry</highlight> out Congress's immigration wishes, no state should be allowed to do so either.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 因为它（政府）不想实现国会的移民愿望，所以也不允许任何一个州这样做。

examination_example.sentence: Facts about the world are waiting to be observed by objective researchers who use the scientific method to <highlight>carry</highlight> out their work.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 关于世界的事实正等待着客观的研究人员去观察，他们用科学的方法开展自己的工作。

examination_example.sentence: New restrictions on <highlight>carry</highlight>-on bags.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 对手提行李的新限制。

examination_example.sentence: More people are trying to overpack their <highlight>carry</highlight>-on bags to avoid checked-baggage fees, though the airlines strongly dispute this.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 越来越多的人试图超额打包他们的随身行李，以避免托运行李的费用，尽管航空公司对此强烈反对。

sense_info_list.en: if a shop/store carries a particular item, it has it for sale

examination_example.sentence: The average supermarket, according to the Food Marketing Institute, carries some 44,000 different items, and many <highlight>carry</highlight> tens of thousands more.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 根据食品营销研究所的调查，一般超市大约出售4400种不同的商品，还有很多超市出售成千上万种商品。

sense_info_list.en: to have sth as a result
sense_info_list.zh: 带有; 带来(某种后果)

examination_example.sentence: Each of these manifestations of growth <highlight>carried</highlight> its own peculiar problems in its wake.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 增长的每一种表现形式都带来其自身特有的问题。

examination_example.sentence: On the other hand, putting your faith in the wrong place often <highlight>carries</highlight> a high price.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 另一方面，把你的信任放在错误的地方往往要付出高昂的代价。

sense_info_list.en: to accept responsibility for sth; to suffer the results of sth

examination_example.sentence: And firms pay staff less because firms <highlight>carry</highlight> the burden of the employment arrangement going wrong.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 公司付给员工的工资更少，因为公司承担了雇佣安排出错的负担。

examination_example.sentence: I'm experiencing increased zeal for working out since I no longer <highlight>carry</highlight> the burden of a disappointing morning weigh-in.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 我对锻炼的热情越来越高，因为我不再承受着令人失望的早晨称重的负担。

sense_info_list.en: support and move someone or something from one place to another
to take sth/sb to a particular point or in a particular direction

examination_example.sentence: We unconsciously associate fast food with speed and impatience and <highlight>carry</highlight> those impulses into whatever else we're doing.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 我们不自觉地将快餐与速度和不耐烦联系在一起，并将这些冲动带到我们正在做的任何其他事情中。

examination_example.sentence: <highlight>Carry</highlight> their plans through
examination_example.sentence_trans: 实施他们的计划

examination_example.sentence: He'll <highlight>carry</highlight> on blogging — not about eating as cheaply as you can — but eating well on a budget.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 他会继续写博客——不是关于尽可能吃得便宜——而是在预算内吃得好。

examination_example.sentence: This temporarily lowers carbon-<highlight>carrying</highlight> capacity.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 这暂时降低了碳承载能力。
